Drug Design Methodology
1. Target Identification (Protein & Ligand/Structures)
1.1. Literature Review (e.g., Google Scholar, PubMed)
1.2. Protein Download (Protein Data Bank, UniProt)
1.3. Compound Search & Download (e.g., PubChem, Ambinter, ChEMBL, IMPPAT, MPDB 2.0)
2. Protein Preparation
2.1. View and delete unnecessary elements (e.g., BIOVIA Discovery Studio Visualizer)
2.2. Protein Active Site Identification (BIOVIA Discovery Studio Visualizer)
2.3. Solve formatting issues for docking (Swiss PDB Viewer)
3. Ligand Preparation
3.1. Merge all ligands into one SDF file (Open Babel)
4. Virtual Screening & Molecular Docking
4.1. Single Docking (PyRx)
4.2. Multiple Docking (PyRx)
5. ADME Analysis
5.1. ADME (Absorption, Distribution, Metabolism, Excretion) Analysis (SwissADME)
6. Toxicological Properties
6.1. Toxicity Prediction (Protox2, admetSAR)
7. Molecular Dynamics Simulation
7.1. Windows-Based (Yasara)
7.2. Linux-Based (Gromacs)
7.3. Web Server-Based (Simlab)
8. MM/PBSA Analysis
8.1. Free Binding Energy Calculation (Yasara)
9. PCA Analysis
9.1. Software-Based (e.g., Minitab 18)
